Zone comment: Presence of Middle Miocene species such as P. sicana. Reworked? Hard to pin an age on this.
Comment (general): Whole sample examined. 10 specimens of P. sicana noted. Also other ambiguous species that may include variants of P. mayeri - these could be N. acostaensis but these specimens have a 'hooked' aperture like mayeri. What is unusual is that other Middle Miocene species are not present which perhaps should be if reworking was a problem.
